content:
A British stockbroker and humanitarian whos' accomplishments remained unknown and unnoticed by the world still today.
Some of their achievements only came to light after 50 years when they where cornered by a television programme.
The British press celebrated him and dubbed him the "British Schindler". In 2003, he was knighted by Queen Elizabeth II for "services to humanity. On 28 October 2014, he was awarded the highest honour of the Czech Republic, the Order of the White Lion (1st class), by Czech President Milos Zeman, nine months before his death, aged 106.
Based on the book 'If It's Not Impossible...The Life of Sir Nicholas Winton,
@AnthonyHopkins plays the older Sir Winton amazingly showing how being humble with a caring focus on others achieves great things.
@HelenaBonhamCarter is plays the mother every child wishes for.
@JohnnyFlynn as the younger Winton shows how true empathy that we all should learn from.
Not taking away from the others in the movie, this is one movie the whole family needs to see, no matter what background, culture, or political leanings, even one for the school circularium.
It is the right mix, even for some like me who would have liked to dive further into some of the issues and obstacles.
@jamesHawes @LucindaCoxon @NickDrake @JoannaLaurie @IainCanning @EmileSherman @GuyHeeley Thank you for what captures the greatest of humanity for generations to come.
My only disappointment was after sitting through all the credits, the movie is dedicated to a few people, but a photo of Sir Winton would help people to further research and learn.
